# Conditional Statements

# if - elif - else

1) Write a program to check if a number entered by the user is odd or even
    Program:-
    n = int(input("Enter a number: "))
    if n % 2 == 0:
        print("Given number is Even number")
    else:
        print("Given number is Odd number")
    Output:-
    Enter a number: 7
    Given number is Odd number

2) Write a program to find the greatest of 3 numbers entered by the user
    Program:-
    A = int(input("Enter A number: "))              |        A = int(input("Enter A number: "))
    B = int(input("Enter B number: "))              |        B = int(input("Enter B number: ")) 
    C = int(input("Enter C number: "))              |        C = int(input("Enter C number: "))
    if A > B:                                       |        if(A>=B and A>=C):
        if A > C :                                  |             print(A,"is greatest number")
            print("A is greatest number")           |        elif(B>=C):
        else:                                       |             print(B,"is greatest number")
            print("C is greatest number")           |        else:
    else:                                           |             print(C,"is greatest number") 
        if B > C:                                   |
            print("B is greatest number")           |
        else:                                       |
            print("C is greatest number")           |
    Output:-                                        |        Output:-
    Enter A number: 9                               |        Enter A number: 5
    Enter B number: 4                               |        Enter B number: 7
    Enter C number: 5                               |        Enter C number: 2
    A is greatest number                            |        7 is greatest number

3) Voting
    Program:-
    age = int(input("Enter you age: "))
    if age > 18:
        print("You eligible to vote")
    else:
        print("you are not eligible to vote")
    Output:- 
    a) Enter you age: 8
       you are not eligible to vote
    b) Enter you age: 20
       You eligible to vote

4) Exam Results
    Program:-
    marks = int(input("Enter your marks: "))
    if marks >= 90:
        print("Grade A")
    elif marks >= 80 and marks < 90:
        print("Grade B")
    elif marks >= 70 and marks < 80:
        print("Grade C")
    elif marks > 70:
        print("Grade D")
    Output:-
    Enter your marks: 96
    Grade A

5) Check whether a number is greater or not
  Program:-
  num = int(input("Enter a number: "))
  if(num>2):
      print("greater than 2")
  else:
      print("less than 2")
  Output:-
  Enter a number: 5
  greater than 2

6) Write a program to check if a number is a multiple of 7 or not
    Program:-
    num = int(input("Enter a number: "))
    if(num % 7 == 0):
        print(num,"is multiple of 7")
    else:
        print(num,"is not multiple of 7")
    Output:-
    Enter a number: 14
    14 is multiple of 7
    Output:-
    Enter a number: 9
    9 is not multiple of 7

7) Traffic light colours 
    Program:-
    light="Green"
    if (light == "Red"):
        print("stop")
    elif (light == "Green"):
        print("Go")
    elif (light == "Yellow"):
        print("Look")
    else:
        print("light is broken")
    print("end of code")
    Output:-
    Go
    end of code
